The paper deals with linear codes, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of random coding and combinatorial arguments suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the algebraic tools used in the paper may also make it relevant to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
